respStmt.persName: Ibn al-Sanūsī, Muḥammd ibn ʻAlī, active 1897

msItem.title: Fatḥ al-quddūs fī sharḥ khuṭbat al-Qāmūs.

supportDesc.extent: 349 leaves : 222 x 160 (170 x 95) mm, bound to 222 x 165 x 65 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribī in black ink; pointed.

binding.p: Unbound; held in folder of brown leather over pasteboard with flap; orange paper sides painted with black and white vine designs; blind tooled frame; reused paper pastedowns. Carrying case of brown leather with flap and ties; marbled paper sides, mostly effaced.

origin.p: Copy completed on 5 Dhū al-Qaʻdah 1298 A.H.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Muḥammd ibn ʻAlī ibn al-Sanūsī (owner's stamps, f. 1r, 348v).
Formerly owned by David Eugene Smith (bookplate inside front cover).
